  "body": "When a node starts up, it first populates its default state config from a genesis file to get common validator set, crosslink records, starting block hashes and shards. By doing that, all the nodes are in sync, and on the same page with each other. \r\n\r\nCurrently, the default state is hard coded in code (ex: `NewGenesisCrystallizedState` in `crystallized_state.go`). Instead of loading the default state in code, we should load it from a JSON config. It is identical to `genesis.json` of geth.\r\n\r\nThe default states are defined in `NewGenesisCrystallizedState` and `NewGenesisActiveState`, let's translate them to a JSON file and have `crystallized_state.go` and `active_state.go` use them.",
